The paper discusses the use of honeybots for enhancing security in social networks, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR). The proposed system, SODEXO, involves the integration of honeybots with social networking sites, which falls under the category of social computing (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the use of quantitative methods for understanding the tradeoffs of honeybots, which is related to systems and control (cs.SD). The use of honeybots for gaining information from botnets involves network security (cs.NI). Finally, the paper discusses the design of a protection and alert system, which is related to cybersecurity (cs.CY).
